author: Dailymail.Com Reporter
title: San Jose declares local state of emergency during floods | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad San Jose declares local state of emergency as hundreds of residents are evacuated after dramatic rescues from 'once-in-a-lifetime' chest-deep flood waters Emergency officials raced to help locals who were caught out by the flash floods that hit on Tuesday morning At least 225 residents were taken to dry land and rinsed off with soap and water to prevent them from being sickened by floodwaters that had traveled through engine fuel, garbage, debris and over sewer lines Residents were seen going door-to-door searching for other people who needed to leave the neighborhood Rains causing floods are coming from atmospheric rivers dumping massive quantities of Pacific Ocean water
